Cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) have been confirmed in Liechtenstein. The Liechtenstein authorities have introduced a number of measures to limit the spread of the virus.
You should comply with any additional screening measures put in place by the authorities.
We recommend that British nationals who wish to leave Liechtenstein to contact their travel operator to make arrangements to do so as soon as possible.
Gatherings of more than 5 people are banned. All restaurants, bars, leisure and entertainment facilities are closed.
Further information
Further information on coronavirus, including advice on preparing for foreign travel and helping reduce the spread of the virus, is available from Public Health England and on the TravelHealthPro website.
